<doc id="302314" wikidata="Q5643201" url="?curid=302314" title="Hallucinations (David Usher album)">
<text>Hallucinations is David Usher&#x27;s third studio album. It was released on September 9, 2003 via EMI label. Two singles, &quot;Time of our Lives&quot; and &quot;Surfacing&quot; were released off the record. &quot;Hallucinations&quot; follows two other solo albums, &quot;Little Songs&quot; (1998) and &quot;Morning Orbit&quot; (2001), and precedes a fourth solo album, &quot;If God Had Curves&quot; (2005). The album debuted at #6 on the Canadian Albums Chart, selling 6,300 copies in its first week. It is Usher&#x27;s highest position on that chart of his solo career.

